IN YOUR HANDS
Pt. 3/5 (Answers EP)

Feeling the unspoken energy of someone through their body beyond their words; I was continually trapping myself inside a web governed by Neptune and the refusal to face reality. ‘In Your Hands’ was the exact point of surrender. I had spent my life forcing situations, exhausting my heart hoping for love where it was not available. For the first time, I was able to let go and trust in something greater.

Written & produced by ALYSS


♅

You got my body in your hands
But you won't take it
You think that I won't understand
But I swear I'm braver
From before, when I was
When I would live in fear
But times change, it's too late
That's when you disappeared

Into the air, I left it
In your hands, in your hands
I know you care, I felt it
In your hands, in your hands
But the gods took you away
To a land, another land
So I won't fight our fate
It's in your hands, in your hands

I know your barrier is cold
We're both the same
The depths we dive no parallel
You're the first i found
Who is not afraid
To go where they won't go
To believe in something
But they're just seeds we throw

Into the air, I left it
In your hands, in your hands
And, oh, you care, I felt it
In your hands, in your hands
But the gods took you away
To a land, another land
So I won't fight our fate
It's in your hands, in your hands

Our hearts beat out of time
But I keep thinkin' 'bout, keep on thinkin' bout
There must be somethin' that
Ain't quite finished yet
I know there is a higher power
I'll hold it

Into the air, I left it
In your hands, in your hands
And, oh, you care, I felt it
In your hands, in your hands
But the gods took you away
To a land, another land
So I won't fight our fate
It's in your hands, in your hands
